WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.840
Let's try Positron Assistant for the first time together, Positron Assistant is a built-in

00:00:03.840 --> 00:00:08.040
AI chat and code helper inside of Positron, powered by large language models like Claude

00:00:08.040 --> 00:00:09.040
and Copilot.

00:00:09.040 --> 00:00:13.160
You get both chat and inline code suggestions, it's data science context aware, sees your

00:00:13.160 --> 00:00:16.400
variables, data frames, plots, console sessions, and packages.

00:00:16.400 --> 00:00:20.280
Step one is to just turn it on, go to the settings menu and enable the Positron Assistant.

00:00:20.280 --> 00:00:24.320
From there you can connect to a provider, using Claude for chat or Copilot for autocomplete

00:00:24.320 --> 00:00:27.080
and you'll see a new assistant pane ready for your first question.

00:00:27.080 --> 00:00:28.760
Step two is just to ask it something.

00:00:28.760 --> 00:00:32.220
Ask questions about what variables and data frames are in my workspace, show me a summary

00:00:32.220 --> 00:00:36.000
of data frame or plot distribution, or any suggestions to clean up this data frame or

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:37.000
improve this plot.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:40.439
You should use Positron Assistant for live context, as it knows your data, flows will

00:00:40.439 --> 00:00:44.680
stay intact, you code, visualize, iterate, all without leaving Positron, and exploration

00:00:44.680 --> 00:00:48.720
is made easy, beginners and pros both get dynamic help with cleaning, plotting, debugging,

00:00:48.720 --> 00:00:49.720
and understanding.

00:00:49.720 --> 00:00:53.000
Ask the model high-level questions, ask it to tweak your code, ask for visualizations

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:54.720
or refactoring suggestions.

00:00:54.720 --> 00:00:57.320
Be sure to leave any questions in the comments below and follow along for more content like

00:00:57.320 --> 00:00:58.320
this.

00:00:58.320 --> 00:00:58.320


